1 The LORD said to me, "Go, show your love to your wife again, though she is loved by another and is an adulteress. Love her as the LORD loves the Israelites, though they turn to other gods and love the sacred raisin cakes." 

2 So I bought her for fifteen shekels of silver and about a homer and a lethek of barley. 

3 Then I told her, "You are to live with me many days; you must not be a prostitute or be intimate with any man, and I will live with you." 

4 For the Israelites will live many days without king or prince, without sacrifice or sacred stones, without ephod or idol. 

5 Afterward the Israelites will return and seek the LORD their God and David their king. They will come trembling to the LORD and to his blessings in the last days.

HEAPS of dogs will run up to me!

today, there was this really sweet white fluffy doggie 
it's about knee-to-waist-high...
i was sitted on one of those benches, facing the river...
and it came running up to me and it stood in front of me and started licking my hand and my face! 
and i could hear its owner screaming from behind
and i turned around, and realised the owner was like on the other end of the field!
that doggie ran all the way to me so i could cuddle it!

they are SO CUTE! (:
but too bad, i never dare throw the ball,
just in case their owner comes up to me and scolds me for having made them walk heaps...

and then, there's those REALLY irritating dogs,
who probably thought,
"Hey! That thing on the grass looks suspicious, it might be a good pee-ing spot"
so they'd walk curiously towards me without me noticing them,
and start SNIFFING me... 
and they'd stare deep into my eyes...
and poke their noses into all my things...
pesky doggies i tell you...
and when they're done sniffing, or when their owners have finally caught up with them,

how rude!

'People ask me, "What is the purpose of life?"  
And I respond: In a nutshell, life is preparation for eternity.  
We were made to last forever, and God wants us to be with Him in Heaven.

We were made by God and for God, and until you figure that out,
life isn't going to make sense. Life is a series of problems:  
Either you are in one now, you're just coming out of one, 
or you're getting ready to go into another one!

The reason for this is that God is more interested in your character than your comfort.
God is more interested in making your life holy than He is in making your life happy.
We can be reasonably happy here on earth, but that's not the goal of life. 
The goal is to grow in character, in Christ likeness.

When I get up in the morning, I sit on the side of my bed and say,
God, if I don't get anything else done today, I want to know You more and love You better.  
God didn't put me on earth just to fulfill a to-do list.
He's more interested in what I am than what I do.  
That's why we're called human beings, not  human doings.

"Happy moments, PRAISE GOD. 
Difficult moments, SEEK GOD. 
Quiet moments, WORSHIP GOD. 
Painful moments, TRUST GOD.
Every moment, THANK GOD. "'
